Obviously a posed photograph.  The First Nation women are wearing nicely adorned clothing, as is the one horse. The women would have worn more utilitarian clothing if they were going to be butchering buffalo but maybe the horse was a &quot;clothes human.&quot;
In any case, First Nation people had long stopped hunting buffalo by the 1900s as white hunters slaughtered the great herds for their skins more than 30 years earlier.
When they did set out to hunt buffalo, they wouldn't have paraded slowly past a white man and his camera as both were few and far between in the days of the great herds.
